@node "dessie" "Description        "

                   @{b}fASt's f1WORLD Update Checker@{ub}

 @{u}Description:@{uu}

 fASt's f1WORLD Update Checker (FFChecker for short) was orignally
 concieved around May 1997 at that time there was no way for me to
 create the program that i wanted.

 I desperately wanted a small utility that would at the press of a button
 tell me if a certain web site had been updated.  At the time there were
 none like that, now however there are several such utilities.

 So that is how FFChecker came to be created and that is what it does.
 Dont load your browser and then the page. Just load FFChecker and let
 it do the work for you.

 After a few months of learning and some great advice from many many
 people the original version of FFChecker was written.  Of course at
 that time fASt's f1WORLD had not been created but it was being thought
 about.

 Almost a year later fASt's f1WORLD was opened and again the thought of
 FFChecker came back (then it was called webchecker).  After a bit of work
 and alot of head scratching, Version 1.0 was released and FFChecker was
 born.
@endnode

@node "install" "Installation       "

                       @{b}fASt's f1WORLD Update Checker@{ub}


 @{u}Installation:@{uu}

 Installing FFChecker is easy,  Just move it to where you would like it
 to be on your system or even floppy disk.
 Double click the FFChecker icon and that is all you have to do.
@endnode

@node "uss" "Usage              "

                    @{b}fASt's f1WORLD Update Checker@{ub}

 @{u}Usage:@{uu}

 Using FFChecker is simple.

 Double click the ffchecker icon and the GUI will open.

 You have four buttons to choose from......

 CHECK
       - Click this to check if fASt's f1WORLD has been Updated.

 ?
       - Loads a small version/information screen.

 Go To fASt's f1WORLD     *

       - This will Load your prefered Web Browser and take you to the
         web site.

 QUIT
       - Quit FFChecker.


 * To use the Web Browser launcher you will have to configure the
   goweb.rexx Arexx script that is included with the archive.

   You have to edit this to point to where your choosen web browser
   is and also the arexx port name of that browser.
@endnode

@node "req" "System Requirements"

                  @{b}fASt's f1WORLD Update Checker@{ub}

 @{u}System Requirements:@{uu}


 FFChecker will work with most amiga's the prefered enviroment would be
 OS.3+, but should be ok with any version.

 The information button will not work if you are not using workbench 3+.

 Arexx must be running before you start FFChecker.

 You also must have a TCP/IP stack running before using FFChecker.

 Rexxreqtools.library & Rxsocket.library must be installed.

 If you have all of these installed everything will work perfectly
 if you find any problems please do let me know.
@endnode

@node "About" "About              "

                       @{b}fASt's f1WORLD Update Checker@{ub}



 


 @{u}PROGRAM HISTORY:@{uu}

 v3.0 Another Major Bug was found in the code. This bug stopped 
      FFChecker checking the website, this problem has now been fixed
      once and for all.  v3.0 is the final release of FFChecker.

 v2.1 Major Bug in v2.0, required small changes to code.

 v2.0 [Final Release]
      A few small changes nothing visible to user. This is the last update.
      Any new versions will be written in a different language or way.

 v1.2 Added Info Button and re-wrote a little of the http source.

 v1.1 Second (almost) Public Release, Now has the option of going to the
      web site via a button.  Cleaned up the code a little.

 v1.0 First Public Release, No real features other than Checking web site.

 v0.9 Crashed every time program quit, small bug fixed.

 v0.5 Added the GUI

 v0.1 First version with working code


