@node "ff" "fASt's f1WORLD     "

                             @{b}@{u}fASt's f1WORLD@{ub}@{uu}
 
                  http://www.f1world.demon.co.uk/f1gp/

                          http://surf.to/f1gp/


 fASt's f1WORLD was officially opened on the 19th July 1998.
 Since then the site has grown and been expanded beyond anything
 that was ever planned.

 Originally to be an Archive of Backdrops for use with Microprose's
 Formula One Grand Prix/World Circuits, the site soon expanded to include
 a countdown to the next Grand Prix clock.

 On the 1st of November the site closed for a 'break'. All files
 were left online and the counter continued to rise.

 On the 1st of November there were 6 exclusive backdrops collections,
 those collections contained 76 different pictures.
 Aswell as that there was a small program to let you play the engine
 notes of some of the top teams.
 There was also the End of Season Results file for the IAF1GPC.

 So what has been happening while the site was closed, I hear you ask well
 read on and you will see.

 There have been 2 main new area's added that we think you will like alot.

 The first was a postcard server so now you can send your friends a
 F1 Postcard from fASt's f1WORLD.

 The second addition was the @{i}f1 live@{ui} area. With the use of a live tv feed
 from German Tv it is now possible to @{b}watch all of the 1999 f1 qualifying
 and races live from fASt's f1WORLD.@{ub}
 (and when there is not any formual one on you can watch german tv)

 In addition to these two areas there have been new backdrops added a F1GP
 utilites section where you can download tools for F1GP.

 So for all your F1GP Needs why not stop by at fASt's f1WORLD.

      http://www.f1world.demon.co.uk/f1gp/ & http://surf.to/f1gp
@endnode

